reviews.title: BUY IN PERSON AND USE IMMEDIATELY

The first time I ordered it for pickup, the squash was fresh and firm, and it roasted well. The subsequent times I ordered it, I received a nearly-expired product. On one of those occasions, the quash spoiled just a couple of days after purchase (yet before the “best by” date). It had almost liquified in the bag, was covered in a white slime, and it smelled horrible. I had to throw it away, and in so doing, I threw away nearly $8. (I had bought two bags).

reviews.review_text: Eh not fond of squishy squash so I cook it right away and freeze or refrigerate for later use. Excellent flavor, full of beta carotene, fiber, vitamins and so healthy. Mash with a bit of butter, salt, nutmeg and white pepper and it’s delicious.
